35 void comparisonTest(const std::string& filename)
36 {
37  // Get the folder that is configured at compile time by CMake
38  std::string comparisons_folder = COMPARISONS_FOLDER;
39 
40  // Open the file
41  std::ifstream file((comparisons_folder + filename).c_str());
42 
43  // If we don't find the input file, then the test should fail
44  REQUIRE(file.is_open());
45 
46  // Load the mixture
47  GlobalOptions::workingDirectory(TEST_DATA_FOLDER);
48  std::string str;
49  getline(file, str);
50  Mixture mix(str);
51 
52  // Load the state variable information
53  getline(file, str);
54  int var_set, n1, n2;
55  std::stringstream s1(str); s1 >> var_set >> n1 >> n2;
56 
57  // Load the function for comparison and tolerance
58  getline(file, str);
59  std::string fun; double tol;
60  std::stringstream s2(str); s2 >> fun >> tol;
61 
62  CompareFunc* function =
63  Utilities::Config::Factory<CompareFunc>::create(fun, tol);
64 
65  // Load the state variables and data to compare to
66  Eigen::MatrixXd data = readMatrix(file);
67  const int result_size = data.cols()-n1-n2;
68 
69  // Close the file
70  file.close();
71 
72  // Loop over the states
73  double v1 [n1];
74  double v2 [n2];
75 
76  for (int i = 0; i < data.rows(); ++i) {
77  INFO("Line:" << i + 4);
78 
79  // Set the state of the mixture
80  Eigen::Map<Eigen::VectorXd>(v1,n1) = data.row(i).segment( 0,n1);
81  Eigen::Map<Eigen::VectorXd>(v2,n2) = data.row(i).segment(n1,n2);
82  mix.setState(v1, v2, var_set);
83 
84  // Now compute the function and compare with expected result
85  try {
86  bool passed =
87  function->compare(mix, data.row(i).tail(result_size));
88  CHECK(passed);
89  } catch (Error& e) {
90  INFO(e.what());
91  CHECK(false);
92  }
93  }
94 
95  delete function;
96 }
